Akure – Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State has disclosed that the Ado/Akure road dualization would be funded with African Development Bank(AfDB) loan. He revealed that arrangements have been concluded by Ondo State government and Ekiti State government to dualize the road. According to a statement by the state Commissioner for Information, Donald Ojogo, Governor Akeredolu and his Ekiti State counterpart, Dr. Kayode Fayemi, were awaiting presidential approval and that of the Federal Executive Council(FEC) before the commencement of construction work on the road. Akeredolu who attended a Special Thanksgiving Service on Sunday with his wife, Betty, his deputy, Agboola Ajayi and some state functionaries at the Christ Apostolic Church (CAC) Mount of Monument of God’s Grace, Otapete, Owo, emphasised that the road after completion would be tolled. He also disclosed that his administration had also perfected plans to construct a dual carriage virgin road from the southern part of the state to Kogi in the north central region. The Governor said: “When done, these roads will be tolled so as to enable the state government have a channel of repaying monies that will be spent on them. “Akure to Ado road, we have written letters to the Federal Government and we are sure that the President will sign it and it will be taken to the FEC. “We are only waiting for the approval of the FEC , the bank , African Development Bank is ready to give us loan to dualize the road and it will be tolled.”